pr_body:
This UI would help us to create various shapes and transform them.

Currently, it supports
- Creation of
  - Line
  - Circle
  - Quad
- Selection (Translation)
- Deletion
- Shapes are perfectly clamped

Demo

![python_Dg9yGkR9DT](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64432063/175497817-21974f43-d82b-4245-b93d-2db1081e6b04.gif)

0th index/id - static icon
1st index/id - pressed icon
So I am updating the icon of the `current_mode` button

pr_body:
In this new feature, we are adding `Polyline` shape to the `DrawPanel`.
We can select the polyline mode from the mode panel and then click on the panel where ever we want to add a point.
You can use right-click to stop the creation of the line anywhere you want.

pr_body:
In this feature, I have basically inherited the polyline code and used it in the freehand drawing.
Instead of adding independent lines, I am using the `Polyline` shape and adding the points depending on the mouse drag event.
Creation looks smooth but it's laggy in terms of translation and rotation.

pr_title: DrawPanel Feature: Adding Rotation of shape from Center
pr_body: Adding a `RingSlider2D` to interactively rotate any shape from the center. Demo:
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 948602473, 'comment_body': 'this test is a bit too lite for me.  You should use `snapshot` to save the scene and check if we have the expected color and the expected number of objects. 

You can look at this example to see how to do it: https://github.com/fury-gl/fury/blob/master/fury/tests/test_window.py#L26-L30
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 18, 2, 49, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'skoudoro', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 948605247, 'comment_body': '`position = position or self.position` instead', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 18, 2, 57, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'skoudoro', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 948605694, 'comment_body': 'same as above: `center = center or self.center` instead of the `if`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 18, 2, 58, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'skoudoro', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 949401929, 'comment_body': 'If I use this, it throws the below error
`ValueError: The truth value of an array with more than one element is ambiguous. Use a.any() or a.all()`.

Should I use something like `center = self.center if center is None else center` ??', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 18, 17, 13, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ganimtron-10', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 949606696, 'comment_body': 'yes', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 18, 21, 12, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'skoudoro', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_body:
This feature adds grouping functionality to the shapes present in the `DrawPanelUI`.
PR #623 needs to be merged before this.

To group shapes:
- Go to selection mode
- Hold the `Ctrl` Key
- Select the shape you want to group together using `left mouse click`
- If you want to ungroup the shape, just select the shape again and it will be automatically deselected.

Features:
- Translation of all the shapes
- Rotation of all the shapes

Demo:
![python_UiElpeke69](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64432063/183248609-4281087c-c930-4141-907a-5a906732524a.gif)


pr_body: Adding `polyline.png` and `polyline-pressed.png` icon required for the `DrawPanel`.

pr_title: Adding resize and freehand drawing icon
pr_body: While adding new features in the `DrawPanel`, to select it from the mode panel we need some extra icons. Adding those icons here to easily fetch them.

As we are adding new features to `DrawPanel`, new icons are used to select and play around with it. Adding those icons to `fury-data` [here](https://github.com/fury-gl/fury-data/pull/11). Updating the `fetch_viz_new_icons` to fetch these icons.
This PR needs to be merged before #695 and #696 .

pr_title: Fixing `ZeroDivisionError` thrown by UI sliders when the `value_range` is zero (0)
pr_body:
Currently, the UI sliders throw `ZeroDivisionError` whenever the `value_range` is zero ie. min_value and max_value are the same.
Adding checks to avoid these errors and setting the handle at the start.

pr_title: DrawPanel Update: Removing `in_progress` paramter while drawing shapes
pr_body:
Currently `draw_shape` method that creates shapes on `DrawPanel` was having a parameter called `in_progress` which was keeping a check on whether the shape are already created or not.
This parameter does give a clear idea as why and for what it is used.
So removing this and separating the functions to make things more clear.

pr_title: DrawPanel Update: Seperating tests to test individual features
pr_body:
As we are now adding new features to the `DrawPanel` the current test is becoming bigger and bigger.
Due to this creating, debugging, and managing tests is becoming harder.
So to keep things simple, separating tests to validate individual parts or features of the `DrawPanel`.

Whenever we create, translate, or rotate the shapes on the panel it sometimes overlaps the `mode_panel` or `mode_text` which are used to select and show the current mode respectively.
eg. 
![python_jHAyyCrRD2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64432063/188268649-65ea24f0-3f46-4545-8e52-e07513a94b9f.gif)

Repositioning the `mode_panel` and the `mode_text` to be outside the panel to solve the overlapping issue.
eg.
![python_OZovev32PG](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64432063/188268804-949ec656-7da3-4310-ba8b-7e4f0281faa1.gif)

pr_title: DrawPanel Update: Moving rotation_slider from `DrawShape` to `DrawPanel`
pr_body:
Currently, each `DrawShape` has its own individual rotation_slider which rotates the shape from the center.
This increases the dependency of `DrawShape` on `DrawPanel` which we don't want.
So moving the rotation_slider to `DrawPanel`, to keep a single rotation slider and avoid excessive memory usage.
